                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>On March 18 Dr. Chaim Weizmann, the Zionist leader who until December 1946 had
                    been President of the World Zionist Congress, discussed the Palestine problem
                    with President Truman. The editors have been unable to find an official record
                    of this conversation. For the President’s later report, see Harry S. Truman, <hi
                        rend="italic">Memoirs by Harry S. Truman</hi> (Garden City, N.Y.: Doubleday
                    &amp; Company, 1956) volume II, page 161.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
